This constructor is intended to be used for variables that are enclosed by another type (e.g. as member in a struct or array) because its name will be set by the enclosing type.       • UInt64

        protected UInt64()
        Constructor that generates a default UInt64 without name and value. This is only allowed for typedefs of extended classes and hence subclasses should provide it public. Variables that are created with this constructor can only be generated as typedef and not as variable definition.
        Since:
        24.0
